com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.firmwares

Class FirmwareFileRequestExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.FileRequestExecutor
      • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.firmwares.FirmwareFileRequestExecutor

  • public class FirmwareFileRequestExecutor
extends FileRequestExecutor
    Request executor provided by FirmwaresApi. Use this class if you want to fetch firmware files through fluent API in chained fashion, for instance: 
       
   KontaktCloud kontaktCloud = KontaktCloudFactory.create();
   String name = "3.1";
   Model model = Model.SMART_BEACON;
   FileData firmwareFile = kontaktCloud.firmwares().fileOf(name, model)
      .forDeviceType(DeviceType.BEACON)
      .execute();
    Keep in mind that device type must be specified so invocation of forDeviceType method is mandatory. Otherwise an exception will be thrown.
